[FEN "2rq1rk1/1p1bppbp/p2p1np1/4nPP1/3NP3/2N1B2P/PPP1B3/R2Q1RK1 b - - 0 13"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2020.11.29"]
[UTCTime "06:12:13"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ Emanuel Lasker just played g5, completely underestimating his opponent's move. By now, I'm sure you see the way forward! }
13... Rxc3! 14. bxc3 { Did you see what would have happened after gxf6? } (14. gxf6 Rxe3 15. fxg7 Kxg7 16. Bf3 Qb6 $19 { This position would have been crushing for black }) 14... Nxe4 15. Bd3 Nxc3 $19 { The knight will quickly spin around back to d5 (and maybe even f6), so why not take a second pawn? Black is not even down any material AND has a perfect pawn structure. } *


